text: Doris Piché (born 14 October 1965) is a Canadian badminton player. She competed in women's singles and women's doubles at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona, and in women's singles and mixed doubles at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:Canadian female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Canada Category:Badminton players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Badminton players at the 1996 Summer Olympics Category:People from Abitibi-Témiscamingue Category:Commonwealth Games medallists in badminton Category:Commonwealth Games silver medallists for Canada
